<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00/963: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the President of the Presidium of the Supreme Council of the
                                Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kalinin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-21">April 21,
                                1939</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have received your friendly message and am glad to learn that your
                            views with regard to my efforts on behalf of world peace are similar to
                            those expressed to me by the heads of numerous other states.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>